Implementation(...)`.\n\nUpdated:\n- `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/X509UtilTest.java`\n\nKey adjustments:\n- `STORE_SPI_CLASS_NAME` now comes from `X509StoreCertCollection.class.getName()` instead of a hardcoded string.\n- Added a direct reachability helper using `new X509StoreCertCollection()` before invoking the dynamic provider lookup paths.\n- Kept coverage focused on public `X509Store.getInstance(...)`, which routes into `org.bouncycastle.x509.X509Util.getImplementation(...)`.\n\nThis should still reach:\n- `ClassLoader#loadClass(String)`\n- `Class#forName(String)`\n- `Class#newInstance()`\n\nwhile ensuring the target Bouncy Castle SPI class is included in the Native Image. I did not run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_062527c6e96fb00e0169fbc340c3e881a283dda4aa30c2a266\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 985, "output": 1254, "cacheRead": 37376, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39615, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778107181088, "responseId": "resp_062527c6e96fb00e0169fbc32deac481a29b133f42a13398d6"}}
